**Course Schedule**

The course will be delivered over 24 weeks, with one module per week. Each module will last 60 minutes, and will include a lecture, discussion, and practical exercise.

**Assessment**

Students will be assessed based on their participation in class discussions and practical exercises, as well as their performance on assignments and projects.

**Resources**

* "Deep Learning Overview" by [Author] (https://example.com/deep-learning)
* "Advanced Concepts" by [Author] (https://example.com/deep-learning-advanced)
* TensorFlow and Keras documentation (https://www.tensorflow.org/ and https://keras.io/)
* Python and NumPy documentation (https://www.python.org/ and https://numpy.org/)

**Prerequisites**

* Prior experience with Python programming
* Familiarity with linear algebra, calculus, and probability
* Basic understanding of machine learning concepts

**Target Audience**

* Advanced students interested in deep learning
* Professionals looking to upgrade their skills in deep learning
* Researchers interested in applying deep learning to their field

**Learning Outcomes**

* Master deep learning at an advanced level
* Apply core concepts of deep learning to real-world problems
* Develop practical skills in deep learning using TensorFlow and Keras
* Design and implement a deep learning project
